modules.description: The module provides functions for inserting, updating, and querying key-value structures with ordered keys, alongside advanced operations like merging, splitting, and traversal. It supports transformation through iteration, filtering, and conversion between maps and sequences, enabling efficient manipulation of ordered data. Specific use cases include maintaining sorted datasets, dynamic key-value updates, and integrating map operations with sequence-based workflows.

Provides a mechanism for tracking dependencies between values and efficiently recalculating only the parts of a computation that have changed. It works with graphs of computations represented as nodes and edges, supporting lazy evaluation and change propagation. Used to build responsive systems where data updates trigger minimal recomputation, such as in real-time data pipelines or interactive applications.

manages ordered key-value stores with efficient updates and queries, supporting operations like merge, split, and traversal. it enables dynamic data manipulation through iteration, filtering, and conversion between maps and sequences. users can maintain sorted datasets, perform incremental updates, and integrate map logic with sequence processing. examples include real-time data synchronization and maintaining ordered indexes with minimal recomputation.
